qas.question: What kind of aircraft is used to intercept and destroy other aircraft?
What particular aircraft did the interceptor target most?
When were interceptors like the F-102 Delta Dagger first built?

answers.text: after the end of World War II

qas.question: When were interceptors like the F-106 Delta Dart not being built anymore?
The interceptors were no longer built because of the shift of the bombing role to what?

context: <a0_0>The interceptor aircraft<a0_0/> (or simply interceptor) is a type of fighter aircraft designed specifically to intercept and destroy enemy aircraft, particularly <a1_0>bombers<a1_0/>, usually relying on high speed and altitude capabilities. A number of jet interceptors such as the F-102 Delta Dagger, the F-106 Delta Dart, and the MiG-25 were built in the period starting <a2_0>after the end of World War II<a2_0/> and ending in <a3_0>the late 1960s<a3_0/>, when they became less important due to the shifting of the strategic bombing role to <a4_0>ICBMs<a4_0/>. Invariably the type is differentiated from other fighter aircraft designs by higher speeds and shorter operating ranges, as well as much reduced ordnance payloads.
